Madison Elementary School
August 16 at 4:49 PM ¬∑

Transportation Tip: Your child only needs to learn/know the first set of numbers for his/her bus. Madison teachers, students and staff will refer to the buses as 15, 46, 51, 52, 76, 84, 86, and 99 and not as 15-17, 46-11, etc.

Any questions regarding your child's bus transportation, should be directed to the Transportation Department at 574-269-1750.

On Mondays, buses will pick up approximately 50 minutes later due to PLC/Late Start every Monday.

shared_text:
Holly Stuffle McCammack‚ÄéWarsaw Rocks!
July 2 at 4:35 PM ¬∑

The #McLittleLibrary is now open and we would love to be a part of #WarsawRocks!! (Located at 116 Fawley St, Warsaw- Near Kelly Park) Feel free to hide rocks around our library set up when you stop by for a FREE book!! We have books for all ages (toddler -adult), we also have a few books in Spanish. We try to stock a book for everyone! If you are looking for something special, leave a note in our guestbook or in the black bin on our porch! We will do our best to find what you are looking for!!
We also have a hitching post, watering hole and free dog treats to keep your pup busy while you find your special book! Feel free to enjoy a seat under our shade book for a bit of relaxation while you read your book!

We hope to see you soon!!
Jayson & Holly (Lolli) McCammack
#LittleFreeLibrary
#WarsawIN
#FreeBooks

shared_text:
Warsaw Community Schools is at Warsaw Community High School.
May 11 at 4:41 PM ¬∑ Warsaw, IN ¬∑

Last week, Warsaw Community Schools held their first milestone moment for seniors with curbside pickup of graduation regalia. The Graduation Taskforce for WCS has been working to finalize graduation plans for the Class of 2020. While following state directives, it is the goal of Warsaw Community Schools to hold an in-person graduation ceremony.

The date set forth is Friday, July 17, 2020 at 7:30 p.m. on the football field, observing social distancing guidelines. Please note, since this is an outdoor event, the first rain date would be Saturday July 18 at 7:30 p.m. and then July 19 at 7:30 p.m.

Further details regarding graduation and milestone moments for WCS seniors will be published on the Class of 2020 Forum on the district, high school, and WACC websites http://warsawschools.org and on social media accounts.

Warsaw Community Schools is in Warsaw, Indiana.
April 30 at 11:49 AM ¬∑ Warsaw, IN ¬∑

As we wrap up Autism Awareness Month, Mrs. Demopoulos would like to share a final book, Armond Goes to A Party: A book about Asperger's and Friendship by Nancy Carlson and her friend Armond Isaak.

Mrs. Demopoulos adds, "It has been so wonderful to share these books with you each week, about autism. I feel so blessed to go to work at Warsaw Community Schools and work with the wonderful staff. I get to be with the most amazing students each and every day. I hope you have enjoyed these books as much as I have enjoyed reading them to you."

Tip of the week:
Individuals with autism may have difficulty generalizing skills from one setting to another. An individual who has learned turn-taking in the classroom setting with peers, may not be able to take turns in the home setting with siblings. These individuals will need to be taught skills in multiple settings as well as with different people and activities/tasks.

post_text: Thursday Thank You!
shared_text:
Warsaw Community Schools is at Lincoln Elementary School.
April 30 at 12:28 PM ¬∑ Warsaw, IN ¬∑

Today, our THURSDAY THANK YOU belongs to all Emergency Workers
Shelby Beam, Lincoln Elementary School, offers a tribute to a few of our hometown heroes: Joel Beam, Mike Wilson, Carl Wireman, Layne Sumner, and K-9 Buddy.

‚ÄúMy husband, Police Captain Joel Beam, Warsaw Fire Department Chief Mike Wilson, Flight Medic Carl Wireman and Police Chaplain Layne Sumner make up a unique team called CISM, Critical Incident Stress Management.

This group has received training in trauma so that they can help and counsel all of our first responders as they respond to repeated trauma and deal with their feelings and emotions after tragic events. These men sit in on the hardest incidents with those who have experienced them and help them process and recover from what they have seen. It is long and hard work, but they run toward it in order to help those who help us on a daily basis. This is in addition to the hard frontline jobs these men maintain on their own.‚Äù

With a heartfelt thank you for all you do to make our community the best place to live, we offer our gratitude! #wcsmission

Autism Awareness Month 2020 Book 2

April 15 at 12:10 PM ¬∑

The book this week for Autism Awareness Month is "My Brother is Autistic" by Jennifer Moore-Mallinos.
We hope you enjoy listening and learning about autism.
Our hope is that you take this information and grow your awareness of those individuals in our community.

Tip of the week:
Break tasks or activities down into smaller steps. Use pictures of the steps, model the steps, and say each step out loud to help the student/individual be successful.

Maria D Demopoulos, MA
Autism Resource Specialist

post_text: E-Learning Extended to May 1st
shared_text:
Warsaw Community Schools is at Warsaw Community High School.
March 19 at 6:53 PM ¬∑ Warsaw, IN ¬∑

In light of Indiana Governor Eric Holcomb‚Äôs press release at 1:00 PM, Warsaw Community Schools will extend the closing of physical school buildings until May 1 in compliance with the executive order.

As previously messaged, Warsaw Community Schools and active student learning continues to stay open through eLearning lessons.

WCS will extend the current plan of a three-day eLearning week on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays while using Tuesdays and Thursdays as waiver days. From now until May 1, students will have the same educational opportunities that went into effect this week.

Additionally, WCS services provided by Food & Nutrition, Transportation, Technology, Teachers, and the WCS Nurse On-Call will also remain the same. Please see FAQs posted on the District Website.

WCS will continue to evaluate the situation and will communicate any changes as they become necessary. All updates will be posted on the District Website at warsawschools.org

WCS will extend the current plan of a three-day eLearning week on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays while using Tuesdays and Thursdays as waiver days. From now until May 1, students will have the same educational opportunities that went into effect this week.

shared_text:
Warsaw Community Schools is at Warsaw Community High School.
March 18 at 10:49 AM ¬∑ Warsaw, IN ¬∑

Today is the first eLearning day! Teachers are working from home and that sometimes means that there is nobody around to take a photo of you...but if at first, you don‚Äôt succeed (with the selfie stick) try, try, and try again. Yep, we‚Äôre learning too:-)

Over the coming days, we‚Äôll share a glimpse into what life is like for our amazing teachers as they plan, create, assign, check for understanding, re-teach, assess, and grade. They are here for you!

Meet Kaylynn Lampen, Department Leader for English Learners at WCHS. She has a great sense of humor, is incredibly kind, and spent Christmas in Bolivia. She recently got engaged - congrats Kaylynn and Brad! Ms. Lampen is here to help, to guide, to encourage, and to support! Here we go Tigers! Please Note: No selfie-stick was hurt during the three attempts to get a good photo:-) #wcsmission

http://bit.ly/Districtelearning
@ Warsaw Community High School
